2 associated account or accounts.
3 (6) (7) (a) A subscribing customer must have an account with the public utility providing the on-bill
4 credit.
5 (b) If a subscribing customer ceases to hold the account for which the on-bill credit is received but
6 has another account in the service territory of the public utility, the on-bill credit must, at the request and
7 designation of the subscribing customer, be transferred to the new account and adjusted to reflect the
8 proportion of generated electricity assignable to the account.
9 (c) If a subscribing customer ceases to hold the account for which an on-bill credit is received, the
10 public utility, at the request of the subscribing customer, shall transfer the on-bill credit to a new eligible
11 subscribing customer.
12 (7) (8) A subscribing customer may choose to assign their proportion of generated electricity to a
13 nonprofit or a public utility's low-income energy share program.
14
15 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Net energy calculation requirements for shared solar energy
16 facilities. (1) A public utility shall grant on-bill credits to a subscribing customer's account for the account's
17 proportion of generation from a shared solar energy facility for each billing period.
18 (2) (a) If the electricity supplied by a public utility for the account of the subscribing customer
19 exceeds the subscribing customer's on-bill credit, the subscribing customer must be billed for the electricity
20 supplied by the public utility, excluding the subscribing customer's on-bill credit.
21 (b) If the subscribing customer's on-bill credit during the billing period exceeds the electricity
22 supplied by a public utility for the accounts, the subscribing customer must be:
23 (i) billed for the appropriate minimum monthly fees for that billing period; and
24 (ii) credited for the excess kilowatt hours generated during the billing period, with the kilowatt-hour
25 credit appearing on the bill for the following billing period.
26 (3) A subscribing customer owns the renewable energy credits associated with the proportion of
27 generated electricity assignable to each subscribing customer receiving an on-bill credit for a proportion of
28 generated electricity from a shared solar energy facility.
