2 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Shared solar energy facility -- safety and reliability. A shared solar
3 energy facility must include, at the shared solar energy facility owner's expense, all equipment necessary to
4 meet applicable safety, power quality, and interconnection requirements established by the commission. The
5 shared solar energy facility owners shall maintain the service of the facility.
6
7 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Public service commission authority -- rulemaking. (1) The
8 commission has the authority to generally implement and enforce the provisions of [sections 1 through 6].
9 (2) The commission shall adopt rules establishing:
10 (a) the applicable bill credit rate for the subscriber;
11 (b) participation opportunities for all customer classes;
12 (c) the reasonable transferability and portability of shared solar energy subscriptions;
13 (d) consumer protection in accordance with existing Montana laws; and
14 (e) nondiscriminatory requirements for participation for shared solar energy facility owners.
15 (3) The commission rules may not remove a customer from the commission's otherwise applicable
16 customer class to participate in a shared solar energy facility.
17 (4) The commission shall adopt rules within 1 year of [the effective date of this act].
18
19 NEW SECTION. Section 7. Codification instruction. [Sections 1 through 6] are intended to be
20 codified as an integral part of Title 69, chapter 3, and the provisions of Title 69, chapter 3, apply to [sections 1
21 through 6].
22
23 NEW SECTION. Section 8. Saving clause. [This act] does not affect rights and duties that matured,
24 penalties that were incurred, or proceedings that were begun before [the effective date of this act].
25
26 NEW SECTION. Section 9. Effective date. [This act] is effective on passage and approval.
